{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01S95hAGejsjGGoS9KKKRocq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. The ingress-nginx controller is already running, there's an otel-collector in the otel namespace, and there's an ingress for otel.example.com routing to otel-echo service.\n\nI need to:\n1. Enable OpenTelemetry in the ingress-nginx controller configuration (via the ConfigMap)\n2. Configure 100% sampling rate\n3. Update the access log format to include trace and span IDs\n\nThe key configmap keys for nginx-ingress OpenTelemetry are:\n- `enable-opentelemetry`: \"true\"\n- `opentelemetry-collector-host`: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"\n- `opentelemetry-collector-port`: \"4317\"\n- `otel-sampler`: \"AlwaysOn\" with a ratio of 1.0 for 100% sampling\n- `log-format-upstream`: needs to be configured with the trace and span ID format\n\nI should verify that ingress-nginx 1.14.1 supports OpenTelemetry, then update the ConfigMap with these settings.\n\nNow I'm constructing the log format string that includes the OpenTelemetry trace and span IDs, and I need to patch the ConfigMap with this configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":776,"cache_read_input_tokens":31224,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":776},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f8c6730-530f-4959-be21-f4dc2d880a4b","uuid":"47c394c2-022b-4860-8c6c-734b08c2c8b5","request_id":"req_011CcMSA1R126HRk5rPi7dym"}
