{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KnFxzLiwS6hfc76gJP1bRP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working end-to-end. The collector received the exact trace with `Trace ID: 36f879495aa742aba7de81d7f6d1f20f` and `ID: ba5c1f6f83971761`, which match the IDs logged in the nginx access log.\n\nHere's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Step 1 — Enable OTel in the ConfigMap:**\nPatched `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap with:\n- `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"`\n- `otel-sampler: AlwaysOn` / `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` / `otel-sampler-parent-based: \"false\"` (100% sampling)\n- `log-format-upstream` set to the requested format with `otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id`\n- `opentelemetry-collector-host` / `opentelemetry-collector-port` (these are parsed by the controller for other purposes)\n\n**Step 2 — Fix the TOML collector endpoint:**\nThe ingress-nginx controller (v1.14.1) writes `/etc/ingress-controller/telemetry/opentelemetry.toml` at startup with `host = \"\"` — the `opentelemetry-collector-host` ConfigMap key doesn't populate this field. The TOML was patched directly to set `host = \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"`, then nginx was reloaded (not restarted) to pick it up.\n\n**Result:** Access logs now contain non-empty `otel_trace_id` and `otel_span_id` for every request, and the OTel collector is receiving the exported spans via OTLP/gRPC on port 4317."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":55535,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":758},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f8c6730-530f-4959-be21-f4dc2d880a4b","uuid":"d92425ad-7b22-4d7d-9938-3191ac3ff0a9","request_id":"req_011CcMSTyeqgiDLekWALU8Qd"}
